article.headline: SE Louisiana 83, Spring Hill 57
article.story: HAMMOND, La. -- Patrick Sullivan scored 17 points to lead five Southeastern Louisiana players in double figures as the Lions routed Spring Hill College 83-57 on Tuesday night. Southeastern Louisiana (5-1), which has won three straight games, jumped out to a 20-6 lead and held a 45-22 margin at halftime. Spring Hill, an NAIA school, capitalized on two scoring droughts in the second half -- the first lasting 5:12 and the second spanning 4:11 -- to pull within 60-49 with 8:32 left. Sullivan hit the first of two jumpers 16 seconds later as Southeastern Louisiana outscored the Badgers 23-8 the rest of the game. The Lions also dished out 22 assists. Gary Dixon added 16 points for Southeastern Louisiana, while Trent Hutchin and Rodney Jones scored 13 apiece and Deshawn Patterson had 12. Nick Brown led Spring Hill with 22 points and Marcus Coleman added 16, all in the second half.
